  "body": "When constructing a react component, I have these concerns:\n\n```\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <div class=\"col s12 m5\">\n         <div class=\"switch\">\n#### dynamic part ####\n          <input type=\"checkbox\">\n          <span class=\"lever\"></span>\n          </div>\n#### dynamic part ####\n      </div>\n    </div>\n```\n1. Put all the css styles and html elements to the render method of a component.\n2. extract ONLY the dynamic part as a component.\n\nI just want to know which scenario is more efficient?\nWould putting all the css styles and html elements into a react component resolves the cross browser (IE8) compatibility problem? \n",
